{
  "id": "tanstack_query_10736",
  "repo_name": "TanStack/query",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/TanStack/query",
  "base_commit": "ad57c81fd32c26cdc6abd24324501178e0e270da",
  "pr_number": 10736,
  "issue_number": 10820,
  "issue_title": "bug(query-devtools): styleNonce prop has no effect because goober 2.1.17+ overwrites the nonce via window.__nonce__",
  "issue_body": "### Describe the bug\n\nPassing `styleNonce` to e.g. `<ReactQueryDevtools>` no longer prevents CSP violations. The `<style id=\"_goober\">` element injected by the devtools ends up with an empty nonce, causing the browser to reject it.\n\nInspecting the element in Chrome DevTools and checking its properties shows `nonce=\"undefined\"`.\n\n### Your minimal, reproducible example\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/tanstack-query-bdtw2gqj?file=src%2Findex.tsx,package.json,vite.config.ts,README.md\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n| Version | StackBlitz                                                                    |\n| ------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Working | [open](https://stackblitz.com/edit/tanstack-query-edrqbyvp?file=package.json,vite.config.ts,src%2Findex.tsx,README.md) |\n| Broken  | [open](https://stackblitz.com/edit/tanstack-query-bdtw2gqj?file=src%2Findex.tsx,package.json,vite.config.ts,README.md) |\n\n1. Create a React app with Vite and install `@tanstack/react-query` and `@tanstack/react-query-devtools` at a version that includes goober 2.1.18 (e.g. `5.94.5`).\n2. Add a `Content-Security-Policy` header with a `style-src nonce-<your-nonce>` directive in `vite.config.ts`.\n3. Pass the same nonce to `<ReactQueryDevtools styleNonce=\"<your-nonce>\" />`.\n4. Start the dev server and open the browser console.\n5. Observe a CSP violation error for the `<style id=\"_goober\">` element.\n\nDowngrading to `@tanstack/react-query-devtools@5.91.3` (goober 2.1.16) resolves the error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPassing `styleNonce` to `<ReactQueryDevtools>` should be sufficient for the devtools to work under a strict `style-src` CSP policy. No CSP violation errors should appear in the browser console.\n\n### How often does this bug happen?\n\nEvery time\n\n### Screenshots or Videos\n\n_No response_\n\n### Platform\n\n- OS: [Windows, Linux]\n- Browser: [Chrome, Firefox]\n\n### Tanstack Query adapter\n\nreact-query\n\n### TanStack Query version\n\nv5.100.14\n\n### TypeScript version\n\n5.8.3\n\n### Additional context\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe [`styleNonce` prop](https://github.com/TanStack/query/blob/359184ebc159513772dff1209bd0beaca39fbbae/packages/react-query-devtools/src/ReactQueryDevtools.tsx#L41) flows into [`setupStyleSheet`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/blob/359184ebc159513772dff1209bd0beaca39fbbae/packages/query-devtools/src/utils.tsx#L307)([`60bd38ca6`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/commit/60bd38ca6c29272cda04fab14ac4779402ea65f4), PR [#6320](https://github.com/TanStack/query/pull/6320)), which pre-creates a `<style id=\"_goober\" nonce=\"...\">` element and appends it to the document head before the devtools render.\n\nThe devtools use [goober](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober) for CSS-in-JS. Goober manages a single `<style id=\"_goober\">` element and, since **v2.1.17** ([`2d9c3085`](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/commit/2d9c3085fbcf7ea47b810ce88eab9f47e2c2efdd)), unconditionally overwrites its nonce on every access:\n\n```js\nel.nonce = window.__nonce__ // added in goober 2.1.17 (#612)\n```\n\nA follow-up fix in **v2.1.18** ([`44334ec0`](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/commit/44334ec0824d7c67aaa84740d655c5c72830dbfb)) corrected the insertion order but kept the `window.__nonce__` assignment.\n\n`window.__nonce__` is goober's documented CSP hook. Since `setupStyleSheet` never set it, goober always overwrote the nonce with `undefined`, either clearing it on the pre-created element or inserting a brand-new element with an empty nonce, causing the CSP violation.\n\n## Why it worked before\n\nPrior to goober 2.1.17, goober had no nonce handling at all. It would find the pre-created `#_goober` element and reuse it without touching the nonce, so `setupStyleSheet`'s approach worked correctly.\n\nThe behavior changed silently when goober added `window.__nonce__` support in v2.1.17 ([`2d9c3085`](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/commit/2d9c3085fbcf7ea47b810ce88eab9f47e2c2efdd)).\n\nThe goober version in this repo's lockfile stayed pinned at **2.1.16** until [`8f0d83438`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/commit/8f0d83438208952e28e53bf1dce3603cc2c48adc) (PR [#9935](https://github.com/TanStack/query/pull/9935)), which bumped it to **2.1.18**. All releases cut after that point ship with goober 2.1.18.\n\n## Version range\n\n| `@tanstack/query-devtools`                                                                                                                                                         | goober in lockfile | `styleNonce` works? |\n| ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------ | ------------------- |\n| **5.93.0** ([`a678f0957`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/commit/a678f0957), [#10069](https://github.com/TanStack/query/pull/10069)) last working                                | 2.1.16             | yes                 |\n| **5.94.4** ([`c613c2253`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/commit/c613c225355502306c5011bb28fe59225cb1262c), [#10309](https://github.com/TanStack/query/pull/10309)) first broken | 2.1.18             | no                  |\n\n## Fix\n\nSet `window.__nonce__` inside [`setupStyleSheet`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/blob/359184ebc159513772dff1209bd0beaca39fbbae/packages/query-devtools/src/utils.tsx#L307) before the element is created or inserted:\n\n```ts\nexport const setupStyleSheet = (nonce?: string, target?: ShadowRoot) => {\n  if (!nonce) return\n  ;(window as any).__nonce__ = nonce // goober reads this on every style element access\n\n  // pre-creation kept as fallback for goober <2.1.17\n  const styleExists =\n    document.querySelector('#_goober') || target?.querySelector('#_goober')\n  if (styleExists) return\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- PR that introduced `styleNonce` / `setupStyleSheet`: [`60bd38ca6`](https://github.com/TanStack/query/commit/60bd38ca6c29272cda04fab14ac4779402ea65f4)(#6320)\n- goober v2.1.17 \u2014 feat: add nonce() for CSP support: [`2d9c3085`](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/commit/2d9c3085fbcf7ea47b810ce88eab9f47e2c2efdd)([release](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/releases/tag/v2.1.17))\n- goober v2.1.18 \u2014 fixed CSP support, apply nonce before appending: [`44334ec0`](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/commit/44334ec0824d7c67aaa84740d655c5c72830dbfb)([release](https://github.com/cristianbote/goober/releases/tag/v2.1.18))\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-27T20:12:25Z",
